165c6d5e-2638-45c0-b844-40dda15c034f.do_description: To make the output, you have to... make a repeating pattern based on which corner tiles are colored. If there is a 7x7 grid with each corner colored except the bottom right, leave the tiles right next to it them black, then make the tiles after those up to the edges the color from the corner. For the one corner in the bottom right simply color the 2 tiles from the bottom and right the respective colors on each side. If there is a 12x12 grid and the corners are colored in the top right and bottom left, start making a pattern that builds each side one tile up at a time, which each side mirroring each other at the end. For another 12x12 that has a colored tile in the top left and bottom right, make an extended pattern of a cut of square, until there are two blank spaces in between to make the pattern. Then fill in each alternating tile afterwards with 6x1 columns. For a 10x10 there is a colored tile in the top left and top right. Make an alternating colored square with black spaces in between up to three layers. Them put two 1x5 rows on each side after with black spaces alternating.
165c6d5e-2638-45c0-b844-40dda15c034f.grid_description: The output grid size... remains the same as the input grid size
165c6d5e-2638-45c0-b844-40dda15c034f.see_description: In the input, you should see... Colored tiles in some corners

7924e29c-cd42-4aec-9315-de2bb8fee63f.do_description: To make the output, you have to...start with the same size and colors of the input. Starting with one of the color blocks, keep the three blocks surrounding it black. Then make the 5 blocks surrounding the 3 black blocks the same color as the original block. Then go to a different colored block and do the same thing. Keep repeating that pattern until the different colors meet in the middle
